## A. Inner rate loop

### Equation

From `src/lib/rate_control/rate_control.cpp:71-86`:

```cpp
Vector3f rate_error = rate_sp - rate;
const Vector3f torque = _gain_p.emult(rate_error)
                      + _rate_int
                      - _gain_d.emult(angular_accel)
                      + _gain_ff.emult(rate_sp);
if (!landed) updateIntegral(rate_error, dt);
```

Per axis i ∈ {x, y, z}:

```
τ[i] = K[i] · ( P[i]·(ω_sp[i] − ω[i])  +  ∫_i  −  D[i]·α[i]  +  FF[i]·ω_sp[i] )
```

where `α[i] = vehicle_angular_velocity.xyz_derivative[i]` is the IMU-computed angular acceleration (no extra filter inside the controller).

### Integrator update (`rate_control.cpp:88-118`)

```
i_factor[i] = max(0, 1 − (err[i] / 400°)²)             # soft I-gain reduction at large errors
∫_i ← clip( ∫_i + i_factor[i]·I[i]·err[i]·dt,  ±lim_int[i] )
```

The lines that would zero `rate_error[i]` when the control allocator reports saturation are present but **commented out** (lines 92-99). Saturation flags are written via `setSaturationStatus()` from `MulticopterRateControl.cpp:244` but currently have no effect on the integrator.

