**Yaw-specific notes:** lower I (0.1 vs 0.2), higher P (0.2 vs 0.15), D defaults to disabled, lower acro max (540°/s). The structure is identical to roll/pitch — only the gain values and stick scaling differ.

**Pitch sign convention:** the negation appears at three sites — manual mode (line 114), Acro mode (line 191), and (downstream) `generate_attitude_setpoint()`. Consistent with PX4 convention where positive stick pitch maps to nose-down.

