```

### Per-axis breakdown — attitude loop

| | **Roll (φ)** | **Pitch (θ)** | **Yaw (ψ)** |
|---|---|---|---|
| Setpoint — Stabilized | stick → tilt magnitude + direction → `q_sp_rp` (`mc_att_control_main.cpp:145-171`) | same coupled tilt path | stick → world yaw rate → integrated to absolute yaw (`mc_att_control_main.cpp:117-129`) |
| Setpoint — Auto | `vehicle_attitude_setpoint.q_d` from `mc_pos_control` | same | same |
| Attitude measurement | `vehicle_attitude.q` (EKF2 ~100 Hz) | same | same |
| Rate measurement (for D) | `vehicle_angular_velocity.xyz[0]` | `.xyz[1]` | `.xyz[2]` |
| **P** | `MC_ROLL_P` = 6.5 | `MC_PITCH_P` = 6.5 | `MC_YAW_P` = 2.8 |
| **D** (KW fork) | `MC_ROLL_D` = 0.0 | `MC_PITCH_D` = 0.0 | `MC_YAW_D` = 0.0 |
| Yaw weight | — | — | `MC_YAW_WEIGHT` = 0.4 |
| Rate clip | `MC_ROLLRATE_MAX` = 220°/s | `MC_PITCHRATE_MAX` = 220°/s | `MC_YAWRATE_MAX` = 200°/s |
| Yaw FF | — | — | `q⁻¹·dcm_z · yaw_sp_move_rate` (line 103) |
| Output | `vehicle_rates_setpoint.roll` | `.pitch` | `.yaw` |

**Stick mapping differences:** in Stabilized, roll and pitch sticks generate a tilt **vector** (magnitude + direction) — they don't independently set φ and θ. Yaw stick produces a world-frame yaw rate that is integrated into the absolute yaw setpoint. This is why pitching a quad from forward to side flight in Stabilized doesn't pass through a "pure yaw" intermediate.

