## C. KnightWerx fork — deviations from upstream

### Commit `76328d9640` — "add -D term to angle controllers"

Author: won <henry@knightwerx.com> · Date: 2024-09-10 · Files modified:

```
 .../px4fmu_common/init.d/airframes/CMakeLists.txt              | 168 +++++++--------
 src/modules/mc_att_control/AttitudeControl/AttitudeControl.cpp |   4 +-
 src/modules/mc_att_control/AttitudeControl/AttitudeControl.hpp |   4 +-
 src/modules/mc_att_control/mc_att_control.hpp                  |   6 +
 src/modules/mc_att_control/mc_att_control_main.cpp             |   8 +-
 src/modules/mc_att_control/mc_att_control_params.c             |  40 +++
```

Key changes:

- `AttitudeControl::update()` now takes `(const Quatf &q, const Vector3f &rates)` instead of just `q`.
- New member `Vector3f _derivative_gain = {0.1f, 0.f, 0.f}` — the header initializer would damp roll only at 0.1, but `parameters_updated()` overwrites this with the param values on boot (defaults `{0, 0, 0}`).
- `setDerivativeGain()` added to the public API.
- New params `MC_ROLL_D`, `MC_PITCH_D`, `MC_YAW_D` (range 0–1, default 0.0) plus updated docstrings labeling them "Roll -D gain", etc.
- `mc_att_control_main.cpp:303` passes `rates` (from `vehicle_angular_velocity`) into `update()`.

**Effective behavior with default params:** mathematically identical to upstream (D=0 everywhere). The fork only diverges when you tune any of the three new params.

### Heading-good-for-control bypass (`mc_att_control_main.cpp:~331`)

A nearby comment reads "bypassing this check as it has been overactively setting false". The path that would reset yaw setpoint on EKF heading-quality drops is disabled. Watch for unexpected yaw drift in flight logs as a result.

### Rate controller — no fork divergence

`git log hotfix..origin/dev -- src/modules/mc_rate_control/ src/lib/rate_control/` returns nothing. The rate-loop files are byte-identical to `origin/dev`. The dormant anti-windup in `rate_control.cpp:92-99` is upstream behavior.

